---
description: Standard implementation workflow
alwaysApply: true
---

For every feature:

1. Read the relevant documentation.
2. Summarize your understanding.
3. Produce an implementation plan.
4. Wait for approval when architecture changes.
5. Implement only the approved scope.
6. Build the affected modules.
7. Fix compilation issues.
8. Run tests.
9. Review for security and quality.
10. Update documentation.
11. Suggest a Conventional Commit.

Do not refactor unrelated code unless explicitly requested.

Prefer small, reviewable commits.